==English==

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[monandæg|mōnandæġ]]'' ‘day of the moon’, from ''[[mona#Old English|mōna]]'' ‘moon’ + ''[[dæg]]'' ‘day’, a translation of {{L.}} ''[[dies lunae]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈmʌndeɪ/, /ˈmʌndi/}}
* {{audio|en-us-Monday.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌndeɪ|-ʌndeɪ]], [[Rhymes:English:-ʌndi|-ʌndi]]

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|s}}

# The first day of the week in Europe and in systems using the ISO 8601 norm and second day of the [[week]] in the USA. It follows [[Sunday]] and precedes [[Tuesday]].

